      <div class="explain">
        <b>Before:</b> repeated manual checks → ambiguity → re-check loops (time &amp; cost <span class="up">↑</span>).<br/>
        <b>After:</b> hash → compare → same/different result → re-verifiable proof (time &amp; cost <span class="down">↓</span>).
      </div>

      <div class="warn">
        SHA-256 does not prove “truth.” It only proves whether bytes are identical (match) or not (mismatch), and enables re-verification.
      </div>

      <footer>Accuracy(4)=Truth(2)=Life(4)</footer>
